It's how they're doing it already while pretending not to by masking it in less
polite terms. Here are the various characterizations, in ascending order of
preference.

            
<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">1</NUMEX>. Cutting a deal. This is the most
noxious formulation, slung as an insult by hawks such as the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Weekly</ENAMEX>
Standard and the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Wall Street Journal</ENAMEX> . "This <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">man</ENAMEX> who is engaged in
